About the job
Looking for a career with purpose? Flygreen is a jet charter broker with a mission to make private aviation sustainable while delivering exceptional travel experiences. We recognize the impact that air travel has on the environment and are committed to making a difference by creating products and services that improve the environment. We are passionate about the potential of electric aviation and intend on operating the world's first fleet of fully electric aircraft, transforming the way people fly. We are looking for like-minded individuals to join our team and help us achieve our mission.

We are looking for a Backend Web Developer with 3+ years of experience to join Flygreen. Your main tasks will revolve around building back-end office systems to increase efficiency and maximize productivity. From implementing new features, to fixing bugs, and automating existing flows, your days will be filled with coding and collaborative teamwork with internal stakeholders.

Duties & Responsibilities:

You will proactively take on technical and product duties to drive solutions and innovations across the company;
Work with modern PHP framework (Laravel);
Write clean, well-documented, and testable code to ensure the reliability and maintainability of the software;
Integrate Rest APIs and GraphQL endpoints into the backend architecture;
Optimize application performance and ensure high levels of security and data protection;
Work with key-value stores (Memcache, Redis) as well as SQL/NoSQL databases (MySQL, Clickhouse);
Collaborate with frontend developers to integrate the backend functionality seamlessly;
Participate in the entire software development life cycle, from concept and design to testing and deployment;


Skills & Requirements:

Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Software Engineering, or a related field (or equivalent experience);
Strong proficiency in Laravel PHP Framework;
Excellent understanding of Rest APIs and experience with GraphQL;
Experience with version control systems, preferably Git;
Ability to connect to remote systems through SSH and Bash;
Ability to make quick decisions and provide out of the box solutions when needed;
Ability to work in a fast-paced and technological environment;
Ability to communicate effectively and efficiently with various stakeholders;
Frontend & full-stack framework knowledge an asset;
Leadership experience an asset.
Please note this is a full-time, in-office position in Montreal, Quebec


